The paper focuses on the security and usability aspects of password managers, which are relevant to the sub-categories of computer security (cs.CR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybercrime and cybersecurity (cs.CY), and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically discusses the impact of password managers on password strength and reuse, which is a key concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves monitoring participants' passwords through a browser plugin, which relates to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the factors that influence users' password creation and management strategies, which is relevant to the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), cybercrime and cybersecurity (cs.CY), and software engineering (cs.SE).
